original: Brynolf, Ragnar Oskar Eskil, jägmästare, Linköping, f. 17/1/91 i Jons-berg, östergötl. 1., av v. konsul Oskar B. o. Amanda Danielsson. G. 20 m. Anna Greta Hedborg. — Utex. fr. skogshögsk. 16. Anst. i domänverket 16, jägmäst. 35, bitr. jägmäst. h. över-jägmäst. i ö. distr. sed. 35. RVO.
translated: Brynolf, Ragnar Oskar Eskil, forester, Linköping, b. January 17, 1891 in Jonsberg, Östergötland County, son of Vice Consul Oskar B. and Amanda Danielsson. Married Anna Greta Hedborg in 1920. Graduated from the Forestry College in 1916. Employed in the State Forestry Service since 1916, became a forester in 1935 and an assistant head forester in the eastern district in 1935. Awarded the Royal Order of Vasa.
